CSS NOTES/SYNTAX
Cascading Style Sheet

Ways of Using CSS
Inline CSS-- This is done directly in the html element
Internal CSS-- Using styleTag  within a single document
External CSS-- This is Linking an external.css file into the html 


create a .CSS file
link your cssFile to your htmlFile (<link rel="")
Id  >> represents an identifier for elements that wont be used anywhere else in the html
class >>  represents an identifier for elements that can be re-used anywhere else in the html(use class preferrably)
CSS Selector:
Selector                Property            Value
<any identifier>{ 
          backgroundColour     yellow
        }


body{
    backgroundColour:
    colour;
    font-family:
    font-size 0px;
    font-weight: normal
    OR
    font- normal 0px sans-serif
    line-height- 0em/0px
    margin-0;
}

.class-name{
    backgroundColour:
    text-colour(or color) 
    margin: auto(this pushes the texts to the center, you can choose any)(spacing the outside of the boxborder)
    margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px(top px right px buttom px left px)
    width: in px or % or rem
    padding: this is spacing inside the border of the box
    padding: top px bottom px
    font-style: italics
    text-decoration: underline(or none)
    text-transform: uppercase(or any option)
    letter-spacing: 0.0em
    word-spacing: 1em
    border: 0px dotted (or anyOption)
    border-radius:0px for curved edges
    text-align: center or top or anywhere

}
